You can define the `FloatWithUnits` struct as follows:
```rust
struct FloatWithUnits {
    value: f64,
    unit: String,
}
```
Then, you can write a `show` method for it like this:
```rust
impl fmt::Display for FloatWithUnits {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "{} {}", self.value, self.unit)
    }
}
```
This `show` method will format the value and unit with a space between them, as shown in the example "1.8 meters".
